# Explicit Waits in Selenium Python

1️⃣ Why Waits Are Needed in Selenium
Modern web applications uses AJAX and dynamic loading.
This means:
    1. When a webpage opens , all elements do not load immediately
    2. Some elements load after few seconds.

Example:
    1. Login button apprears after page loads
    2. Search results appears after API response
    3. Dropdown options load dynamically

    If selenium tried to locate an elements before it loads , it will throw an error such as:
    1. NoSuchElementException
    2. ElementNotVisibleException

To solve this problem , selenium uses waits.

2️⃣ Types of Waits in Selenium
Selenium provides TWO types of waits.
1. Implicit wait
    -> Applies to the entire script
    -> Selenium waits globally before locating elements

2. Explicit wait
    -> Applies to the specific elements
    -> Waits until a particular condition is met

3️⃣ What is Explicit Wait?
Explicit wait tells selenium:
    Wait until a speific condition occurs before continuing the program

    Example:
        1. Wait until element appears
        2. Wait until element is visible
        3. Wait until element is clickable
        4. Wait until page title changes

Instead of waiting a fixed time , selenium waits only as long as needed.

4️⃣ How Explicit Wait Works
Explicit wait uses TWO Things.
    1. WebDriverWait
    2. Expected Conditions

    Syntax:
    -------
    WebDriverWait(driver , time).until(condition)

    Example:
    --------
    element=WebDriverWait(driver , 10).until(
        EC.presence_of_element_located(By.ID , "myDynamicElememt)
    )

    Explanation:
    ------------
    1. Selenium waits maximum 10 seconds
    2. It checks every 500 milliseconds
    3. As soon as the element appears , execution continues.

If the element is not found in 10 seconds, 
❌ TimeoutException is raised.

5️⃣ Example Code

from selenium import webdriver
from selenium.webdriver.common import By
from selenium.webdriver.support.ui import WebDriverWait
from selenium.webdriver.support import expected_condition as EC

driver=webdriver.FireFox()
driver.get("https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/")
element=WebDriverWait(driver , 10).until(EC.presence_of_element_located(By.LINK_TEXT , "Courses"))
element.click()

    Step-by-Step Flow
    -----------------
    1. Browser opens GeekForGeeks page
    2. Selenium waits up to 10 seconds
    3. It searches for courses link
    4. When the element appears
    5. Selenium clicks the element

6️⃣ Common Expected Conditions
Some commonly used conditions:
Condition & purpose
--------------------
    1. title_is -> waits until title matches
    2. title_contains -> Waits until contains text
    3. presence_of_element_located -> waits until element exists in DOM
    4. visibility_of_element_located -> Waits until elment is visible
    5. presence_of_all_elements_located -> Waits until multiple elements appear
    6. element_to_be_clickable -> Waits until element is clickable
    7. alert_is_present -> Waits until alert popups appears

    Example:
        EC.element_to_be_clickable((By.ID, "login"))
    
7️⃣ Default Polling Time
WebDriverWait checks conditio every:
    ⏱ 500 milliseconds (0.5 seconds)

    Example timeline:
    -----------------
    0 sec -> check
    0.5 sec -> check
    1.0 sec -> check
    1.5 sec -> check

    Until:
    -----
    ✔ Condition becomes true
    OR
    ❌ timeout occurs

8️⃣ Explicit Wait vs sleep()
    time.sleep()
        time.sleep(10)

    Problems:
    --------
    Always waits full 10 seconds
    Slows automation

    ExplicitWait()
    WebDriverWait(driver , 10)

    Advantages:
    -----------
    1. waits only until element appears
    2. faster execution
    3. better automation practice

9️⃣ Advantages of Explicit Wait
    1. Handles dynamic web elements
    2. Improves test reliablity
    3. Aviods unnecessary delays
    4. Prevent element not found errors

🔟 Simple Real-Life Example
Imagine Ordering food online:
    . If the restaurant takes 3 seconds to confirm order
Using slee(10) -> still waits 10 seconds
Using ExplicitWait -> you continue as soon as the order is confirmed(3 seconds)